**Creating summary for research**

I need to generate a summary with citations from "Research Notes", "Rigorous Proofs", and "Verifier Summary." The goal is to keep the summary concise, no more than 200 words, ideally around 120-160 words. I'll draft this carefully while ensuring it adheres to the specified length. content.text: {"summary_md":"This round proved core local structure for finite Whitney triangulations of the disk and substantially advanced the clique-classification program. Proven: G is K4-free so primal maximal cliques are facial triangles; the link of any interior vertex is a chordless cycle (hence interior degree ≥4) and T(v) (faces at v) is a maximal clique of kG; any fully interior face t yields N(t) that induces a maximal K4 in kG; kG is connected for ≥2 faces. New tools: a local Helly lemma across an interior edge and a shared-edge classification (any maximal clique containing two faces on an interior edge equals T(u), T(v), or C(t)/C(g)). A three-triangle lemma shows any three pairwise-intersecting facial triangles with no common vertex and no shared edge are the three neighbors of a fully interior face (hence extend to C(t)). Corrections: size-3 T(v) can be maximal; an earlier outerplanar Helly claim was false (hexagon counterexample). Remaining major gaps: classify maximal cliques with no edge-sharing pair and formalize the outerplanar ear-removal induction. Citations: Research Notes; Rigorous Proofs; Verifier Summary.","one_line_summary":"Shared-edge clique classification proved; non-edge-sharing cliques and outerplanar induction remain.","highlights":["G is K4-free ⇒ primal maximal cliques are exactly facial triangles.","Link of any interior vertex is a chordless cycle ⇒ interior deg≥4 and T(v) is a maximal clique in kG.","A fully interior face t yields N(t) which induces a maximal K4 in kG.","Local Helly across an interior edge: a face meeting both incident faces must contain one endpoint; used in classification.","Proposition: any maximal clique containing two faces sharing an interior edge equals T(u), T(v), or C(t)/C(g).","Three-triangle lemma: three pairwise-intersecting faces with no common vertex and no shared edge are the three opposite neighbors of a fully interior face (so extend to C(t)); note size-3 T(v) can be maximal and an outerplanar Helly claim was refuted."],"next_questions":["Prove the Helly-type statement for pairwise-intersecting facial triangles with no shared edges (classify all non-edge-sharing maximal cliques).","Formalize an ear-removal induction for outerplanar (no interior vertices) triangulations to track maximal cliques under k and deduce k-nullness.","Exhaustively generate small disk Whitney triangulations (n≤20 faces; interior degrees 4–5) to test the classification and search for counterexamples."]}
